the candidate was vague about whether he still believes that 
poland should have nuclear weapons as he wrote in a selfpublished 
book issued in september when he returned to poland after 21 years 
and decided to run for president 
tyminski said the country is sinking because of the 
governments economic reforms which seek to create a capitalist 
system from the socialist economy he said the economic situation 
is worse now then under the communists 
i think quick changes are possible tyminski said first 
we have to open government books and find out truth because those 
books have been closed 
walesa acknowledged many hopes were not realized but said 
quick results are not possible 
i am convinced that i can lead polish reforms to achieve what 
other candidates propose but in a realistic way and not a dreaming 
way walesa said 
