plant 42 where the jet went down 
plant 42 is a highly secure air force installation in the 
antelope valley where northrop corp builds the b2 stealth 
bomber palmdale is about 50 miles north of downtown los angeles 
the crash occurred on air force plant facilities said los 
angeles county sheriffs sgt kennedy westfall the pilot ejected 
and parachuted out he landed on air force property 
the f16 was from the 58th tactical training wing of the 310th 
tactical training squadron at luke 
the pilot capt craig fisher was the only person aboard he 
was in good condition ms sadler said 
a board of officers will investigate the crash authorities 
provided no information about what kind of trouble the plane 
