lebanese officials said saturday they 
will file a un complaint against israel for repeated air raids on 
palestinian guerrilla bases 
israeli fighter jets saturday staged the second attack in a week 
north of its selfdesignated security zone in southern lebanon 
five guerrillas were wounded police said 
lebanons foreign ministry said it instructed its delegates at 
the united nations to lodge a complaint with the security council 
about israels repeated violation of lebanons sovereignty it 
was not certain when the complaint would be lodged 
police said two israeli jets fired four rockets saturday into a 
base used by the libyanbacked palestine popular struggle front in 
the syrianpoliced bekaa valley 
a police spokesman who cannot be identified under standing 
regulations said the guerrillas fired antiaircraft guns but no 
hits were reported 
the estimated 20000 syrian soldiers deployed in the bekaa were 
not involved in the action police said 
the spokesman said the israeli rockets scored direct hits on a 
onestory building used by the struggle front as its local 
headquarters in the bekaa town of taalabaya about 43 miles north 
of the israeli border 
the israeli military said the raid was in retaliation for an 
attempted infiltration nov 20 by struggle front guerrillas in 
south lebanon an israeli lieutenant was killed along with four 
guerrillas in a firefight 
a struggle front spokesman in beirut said we lost contact 
with the base immediately after it was attacked 
the spokesman who refused to be identified said the guerrillas 
were expecting the attack and evacuated most of their positions in 
lebanon the front headed by samir ghosheh is a hardline faction 
within the palestine liberation organization 
the raid was israels 20th air strike in lebanon this year by 
police count 20 people have been killed and 67 wounded in the air 
raids 
on tuesday israeli warplanes blasted a base used by palestinian 
terrorist mastermind abu nidals fatahrevolutionary council 
faction near the southern port city of sidon the planes also hit a 
nearby base manned by the marxist democratic front for the 
liberation of palestine five guerrillas were killed 
earlier tuesday guerrillas of the popular front for the 
liberation of palestine clashed with an israeli patrol in south 
lebanon killing five israeli soldiers and eight guerrillas 
there have been growing attempts by palestinian guerrillas to 
attack israels security zone which was established after israel 
invasion troops withdrew from most of lebanon in 1985 the zone 
ranges from two to 10 miles wide 
palestinian guerrillas have agreed to withdraw from the apple 
province in southern lebanon to allow the lebanese army to deploy 
in the area the government announced friday 
palestinians deployed in the province earlier this year in an 
