cattle swerved to avoid a car and overturned about 40 head 
escaped but the rest remained trapped inside arnold said 
the driver was not hurt three of the animals died on impact and 
two had to be killed 
the same blocks in the early 1870s marked the end of the 
chisholm trail for texas longhorns which were then driven up to 
the towns stockyards said minor who wrote a book on the era 
